to Create Tumblr slideshow in WordPress....</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/create-tumblr-slideshow/">How to Create a Tumblr slideshow in WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Nishtha Dosaj";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8078:"<p>Tumblr is a social networking platform with a host of interesting content like images, videos, quotes, etc. What if you could simply pull this content on your site to create a Tumblr slideshow.</p>\n<p>In this walkthrough, we are going to guide you on How to Create Tumblr slideshow in WordPress.</p>\n<h2>Creating a Tumblr Slideshow in WordPress</h2>\n<h4><strong>STEP ONE : Installation</strong></h4>\n<p>You will first need to install and activate the <a href="http://slidedeck.com/pricing/">SlideDeck3 Plugin</a> .</p>\n<p>Before you start creating Tumblr Slider, you need to have an account on <a href="https://www.tumblr.com">Tumblr</a> and must have the image gallery setup in it. Also, you need <strong>OAuth Consumer Key </strong></p>\n<p>Here are the steps to get your own <strong> OAuth Consumer Key</strong></p>\n<p><strong> Log in to Tumblr  » Navigate to this link &#8211; <a href="https://www.tumblr.com/oauth/apps">https://www.tumblr.com/oauth/apps </a></strong><strong>» Click on register application</strong></p>\n<p><strong> Fill in this Registration Form</strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19065 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/www.tumblr.com_2016-11-02_15-09-45-300x580.png?x36543" alt="Tumblr slideshow for WordPress" width="300" height="580" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/www.tumblr.com_2016-11-02_15-09-45-300x580.png 300w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/www.tumblr.com_2016-11-02_15-09-45-768x1483.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/www.tumblr.com_2016-11-02_15-09-45.png 882w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></p>\n<p>You can find the OAuth Consumer Key once you fill in the form</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19066 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/oAth_Consumer_key.png?x36543" alt="OAuth consumer key - Tumblr" width="889" height="87" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/oAth_Consumer_key.png 889w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/oAth_Consumer_key-580x57.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/oAth_Consumer_key-768x75.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 889px) 100vw, 889px" /></a></p>\n<p><strong> Once you get the Consumer Key, you need to copy and paste it in Advanced options </strong><strong> »</strong> “Last used Tumblr OAuth Consumer Key” and click on Update Options</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19070 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/TumblrApiKeyOption-580x210-580x210.png?x36543" alt="WordPress Tumblr" width="580" height="210" /></a></p>\n<h4>STEP TWO : Create Slider</h4>\n<p>Visit <strong>SlideDeck3 » Manage</strong> and select <strong>Create SlideDeck</strong> under <strong>Dynamic Slider </strong></p>\n<h4>STEP THREE : Integrating <strong>Tumblr</strong></h4>\n<p>Select <strong>Tumblr</strong> as a Dynamic Source</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19071 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/dynamic-source-tumblr-554x580.png?x36543" alt="WordPress Tumblr" width="554" height="580" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/dynamic-source-tumblr-554x580.png 554w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/dynamic-source-tumblr.png 557w" sizes="(max-width: 554px) 100vw, 554px" /></a></p>\n<h4>STEP FOUR : Configure <strong>Tumblr</strong> Source</h4>\n<p>Now it’s time to create your first <strong>Tumblr</strong> slider.</p>\n<p>Give a name to your slider <strong>»</strong> Add <strong>Tumblr</strong> <strong>Blog name</strong> and <strong>Post type</strong> <strong>»</strong> Click <strong>Apply<br />\n</strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19069 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blogname-580x369.png?x36543" alt="Tumblr slideshow" width="580" height="369" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blogname-580x369.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blogname-768x489.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blogname-285x180.png 285w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blogname.png 941w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19068 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/blogname-settings.png?x36543" alt="WordPress Tumblr" width="357" height="279" /></a></p>\n<h4>STEP FIVE : Save Slider</h4>\n<p>Click Save <strong>SlideDeck Button</strong> to save all the settings .</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-18878 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Save_Slidedeck.png?x36543" alt="SlideDeck3 - WordPress" width="124" height="33" /></a></p>\n<h4>STEP SIX : Add the slider to a post or page</h4>\n<p>You’re almost done. It’s time to publish your slider to a post or page. Select any of three available ways to publish the slider on your site.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-18928 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/publish-methods.png?x36543" alt="WordPress slider - SlideDeck3" width="466" height="486" /></a></p>\n<p>That’s it. You are all set to have a slider with photos or videos sourced from Tumblr. Another article that you might also want to check out is <a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/creating-full-width-wordpress-slider/" target="_blank">How to create a full width WordPress Slider.</a></p>\n<p>If you like this article, then please follow us on <a href="http://facebook.com/slidedeck/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Facebook</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/SlideDeck" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Twitter</a> for updates and more articles <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/72x72/1f642.png" alt="????" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<p>If you have any questions or feedback, let us know in the comments section below.</p>\n<br/><br/><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog"><img src="//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg?x36543" alt="Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck" style="display:block;border:none;"/></a><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/create-tumblr-slideshow/">How to Create a Tumblr slideshow in WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=mXTrGHfxQfk:n0BsSAYsJrw:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=mXTrGHfxQfk:n0BsSAYsJrw:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src=