link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Slidedeck/~3/XkuUeKm_TWQ/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"https://www.slidedeck.com/create-wordpress-member-directory/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 17 Nov 2016 08:00:59 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"General";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Tutorials";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"Member directory";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"tutorial";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"UserPro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34:"https://www.slidedeck.com/?p=19211";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:598:"<p>Are you looking to create a WordPress member directory? Now you can easily create a member directory using UserPro Plugin. UserPro automatically creates a list of all the users on your network, with avatars, pagination, and a built-in search.You can also add categories and custom search filters to your member directory using...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/create-wordpress-member-directory/">How to create a WordPress member directory?</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"madhulika";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8818:"<p>Are you looking to create a WordPress member directory?</p>\n<p>Now you can easily create a member directory using <a href="http://userproplugin.com/userpro/">UserPro Plugin</a>. UserPro automatically<span data-swiftype-index="true"> creates a list of all the users on your network, with avatars, pagination, and a built-in search.You can also add categories and custom search filters to your member directory using UserPro Plugin.</span></p>\n<p>In this tutorial, we will give you a quick walkthrough on how to setup a WordPress member directory.</p>\n<h2>Creating a WordPress member directory:-</h2>\n<p>First, you need to install and activate the <a href="https://codecanyon.net/item/userpro-user-profiles-with-social-login/5958681">UserPro Plugin</a>. For more details, see this step by step guide on <a title="Step by step guide on How to Install a WordPress Plugin" href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/">how to install a plugin in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>Upon activation, you can find <strong>Member Directory</strong> Page into your <strong>WordPress Dashboard</strong> &gt; <strong>Pages Menu</strong>.</p>\n<p><a href="http://userproplugin.com/userpro/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19243 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Memdirpage-580x122.png?x36543" alt="WordPress member directory" width="580" height="122" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Memdirpage-580x122.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Memdirpage-768x161.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Memdirpage.png 995w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>In Member Directory Page find below shortcode :</strong></p>\n<p><code>[userpro template=memberlist] </code></p>\n<h4>Setup<strong> Shortcode Options :</strong></h4>\n<p>There are a number of shortcodes available in UserPro plugin to customize the shortcode and can be assigned as a pair option=value in your shortcode like this.</p>\n<p><code>[userpro template=memberlist option=value]</code></p>\n<p><strong>Find some of the shortcode options below :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>exclude</strong> &#8211; Hide specific users from appearing in the member directory. e.g. 1,3,10 will hide these users from the member list.</li>\n<li><strong>search</strong> &#8211; Turn on/off member search in the member directory. Default: 1 (turned on)</li>\n<li><strong>per_page</strong> &#8211; How many members to display per each page. Default: 1</li>\n<li><strong>memberlist_v2</strong> &#8211; This can turn on/off the member directory (version 2). Default: 1 to use the new member directory layout.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Example :</strong></p>\n<p><code>[userpro template=memberlist exclude=1]</code></p>\n<p>This will exclude the member who&#8217;s member user id is &#8216; 1 &#8216;.Like this, you can add a number of options into your shortcode. You can also add custom filtering available for all custom fields, including showing users per specific custom field, or role, etc.</p>\n<p><a href="http://userproplugin.com/userpro/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19244 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/member1.png?x36543" alt="member directory WordPress" width="984" height="1119" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/member1.png 984w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/member1-510x580.png 510w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/member1-768x873.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 984px) 100vw, 984px" /></a></p>\n<h3>Display Members using v1 style</h3>\n<p>You can use it to display rounded profile picture of your members, and also supports search, filtering, and pagination.</p>\n<p><code>[userpro template=memberlist memberlist_v2=0]</code></p>\n<p><a href="http://userproplugin.com/userpro/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19246 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/member2-477x580.png?x36543" alt="member directory WordPress" width="477" height="580" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/member2-477x580.png 477w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/member2.png 558w" sizes="(max-width: 477px) 100vw, 477px" /></a></p>\n<h3>How to Embed This Shortcode with PHP :</h3>\n<p><code>&lt;?php echo do_shortcode(''[userpro template=memberlist]''); ?&gt;</code></p>\n<h2>Setting up an Enhanced Members Directory</h2>\n<p>For creating an enhanced member directory, you need to add that page using below shortcode :-</p>\n<p><code>[userpro template=emd]</code></p>\n<p><a href="http://userproplugin.com/userpro/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19251 size-medium" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/emd-580x332.png?x36543" alt="emd" width="580" height="332" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/emd-580x332.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/emd-768x439.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/emd.png 1284w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>The enhanced member directory list supports pagination, and unlimited custom filtering/sorting options giving you a flexible way to showcase and present your members and choose which custom fields appear for each member.</p>\n<p><strong>Find some of the shortcode options below :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>emd_filters</strong> &#8211; Show/hide search and filters on the sidebar of members. 0 to disable filters, and 1 to enable. Default: 1</li>\n<li><strong>emd_thumb</strong> &#8211; Avatar size as number only. e.g. 200 will display profile photos 200px wide.</li>\n<li><strong>emd_fields</strong> &#8211; A comma-separated list of custom fields to show for each user in list, e.g. emd_fields=first_name,last_name,gender,country will display name, gender and country. This option uses custom field keys.</li>\n<li><strong>emd_paginate</strong> &#8211; Enable/disable pagination in EMD shortcode, default: 1 to enable pagination</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>How to Make Custom Search Filters in EMD?</h2>\n<h4>Example 1: Make Gender as Custom Filter</h4>\n<p>Use this in your shortcode: <code>emd_gender="Gender,radio"</code></p>\n<p>The first part is the label that appears and presents your new filter, the 2nd part &#8220;radio&#8221; will make the filter choices as radio buttons.</p>\n<p><strong>Example :</strong></p>\n<p><code>[userpro template=emd emd_gender="Gender,radio"]</code></p>\n<p>If you do not set radio or dropdown for the filter, it will be a default search input/text. You can make unlimited custom search filters using this method, including custom fields you created by using this pattern. emd_{custom_field}=&#8221;Label,type&#8221; in your emd shortcode.</p>\n<p>I hope this article helped you setup a WordPress member directory. It&#8217;s an awesome way to share your things with specific people or friends on your own website and keep it private.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions/feedback, please let me know in the comments.</p>\n<br/><br/><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog"><img src="//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg?x36543" alt="Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck" style="display:block;border:none;"/></a><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/create-wordpress-member-directory/">How to create a WordPress member directory?</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=XkuUeKm_TWQ:HHqdT2XOr2Q:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=XkuUeKm_TWQ:HHqdT2XOr2Q:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=XkuUeKm_TWQ:HHqdT2XOr2Q:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=XkuUeKm_TWQ:HHqdT2XOr2Q:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=XkuUeKm_TWQ:HHqdT2XOr2Q:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=XkuUeKm_TWQ:HHqdT2XOr2Q:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=XkuUeKm_TWQ:HHqdT2XOr2Q:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=XkuUeKm_TWQ:HHqdT2XOr2Q:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Slidedeck/~4/XkuUeKm_TWQ" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://www.slidedeck.com/create-wordpress-member-directory/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s: