ng";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"layerpro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"layerpro slider";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"SlideDeck";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:8;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"wordpress slider";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:9;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:23:"WordPress Slider Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34:"https://www.slidedeck.com/?p=19123";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:568:"<p>Looking for a tool to build beautiful and responsive animated sliders for your site? You are at the right place. Here is an awesome way to put dynamic a WordPress animated slider on your site in minutes. With SlideDeck3 LayerPro lens, you can now create awesome animated sliders with multiple...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/wordpress-animated-slider-blog/">Setting up a WordPress Animated Slider for Your Blog</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Nishtha Dosaj";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8858:"<p>Looking for a tool to build beautiful and responsive animated sliders for your site? You are at the right place. Here is an awesome way to put dynamic a WordPress animated slider on your site in minutes.</p>\n<p>With SlideDeck3 LayerPro lens, you can now create awesome animated sliders with multiple layers of images and text. LayerPro allows you to add super-smooth animation effects in the form of transition, rotation, and scaling.</p>\n<p>In this article, we will guide you on how to create an animated slider for your WordPress site in just a few clicks.</p>\n<h2>Creating a WordPress animated slider</h2>\n<h3>STEP One: Installation</h3>\n<p>First, you need to install and activate the <a title="Description of the Pinterest Addon" href="http://slidedeck.com/pricing/">SlideDeck3 Plugin</a> and the LayerPro Lens.</p>\n<p><span id=":7y.co" class="tL8wMe EMoHub" dir="ltr">Here is a quick tutorial on how to install SlideDeck lenses in WordPress</span></p>\n<h3>STEP TWO: Create Slider</h3>\n<p>Now it’s time to create your first slider with LayerPro Lens.</p>\n<p>Visit <strong>SlideDeck3 » Manage</strong> and click <strong>Create SlideDeck </strong>under <strong>Custom Content.</strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19154 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Custom-content.png?x36543" alt="LayerPro - WordPress animated slider" width="411" height="145" /></a></p>\n<p>Give a name to your Slider</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19155 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/name.png?x36543" alt="LayerPro for SlideDeck3" width="354" height="45" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Note: <span id=":7u.co" class="tL8wMe EMoHub" dir="ltr">Layer Pro lens only works with Image SlideDecks under Custom Content option.<br />\n</span></span></p>\n<h3>STEP THREE: Integrating LayerPro Lens with Slider</h3>\n<p>Now you need to integrate your favorite lens LayerPro with your Slider.</p>\n<p>Click <strong>Lenses</strong> under <strong>OPTIONS </strong>Tab and Select <strong>LayerPro Lens</strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19138 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lenses-tab-580x230.png?x36543" alt="LayerPro lens for SlideDeck3" width="580" height="230" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lenses-tab-580x230.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lenses-tab-768x305.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/lenses-tab.png 1096w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Make Navigation and Playback settings as per your requirement.</p>\n<p>Create an <strong>Image Slider </strong>by adding few images.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19156 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/imageslide.png?x36543" alt="animated slider WordPress" width="349" height="312" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19157 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/images-580x367.png?x36543" alt="animated slider WordPress" width="580" height="367" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/images-580x367.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/images-285x180.png 285w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/images.png 596w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>Now you need to edit your slides properties.<strong> Go to Slides &#8211; Edit Slide</strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19139 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/edit-slide.png?x36543" alt="Slider - LayerPro lens" width="557" height="164" /></a></p>\n<p>Select <strong>Add Layers</strong> option on right top corner.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19146 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Add-Layer-580x229.png?x36543" alt="SlideDeck3 - WordPress slider" width="580" height="229" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Add-Layer-580x229.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Add-Layer.png 594w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>Click <strong>Add Layer </strong>button<strong><br />\n</strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19144 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/add-layer-1.png?x36543" alt="Add layer - SlideDeck3" width="459" height="369" /></a></p>\n<p>At this point, you have two options available. You can add an <strong>image or text</strong> as a layer of your slider. Let&#8217;s discuss one by one.</p>\n<h4>Creating Image Layer Slider</h4>\n<p><strong>Upload a Layer Image </strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19141 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/uploadimage-580x547.png?x36543" alt="Image layer - SlideDeck3" width="580" height="547" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/uploadimage-580x547.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/uploadimage.png 585w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Make other required settings for the layer Image and click <strong>Apply</strong>.</p>\n<h4>Creating Text Layer Slider</h4>\n<p><strong>Add the Layer Text</strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19145 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Text-layer-1-552x580.png?x36543" alt="text layer - SlideDeck3" width="552" height="580" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Text-layer-1-552x580.png 552w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Text-layer-1.png 589w" sizes="(max-width: 552px) 100vw, 552px" /></a></p>\n<p>Make other required settings for the layer text and click <strong>Apply</strong>.</p>\n<p>You can also add multiple layers on the slide of your slider using <strong>Add Layer</strong> button. It can be either text or image.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19143 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/add-multiple-layer-553x580.png?x36543" alt="Multiple layers for sliders" width="553" height="580" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/add-multiple-layer-553x580.png 553w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/add-multiple-layer.png 584w" sizes="(max-width: 553px) 100vw, 553px" /></p>\n<p>And you are done!</p>\n<p>Hope this article helped you setting up an animated slider for your WordPress blog. Any Questions/Feedback. Let me know in the comments below.</a></p>\n<br/><br/><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog"><img src="//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg?x36543" alt="Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck" style="display:block;border:none;"/></a><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/wordpress-animated-slider-blog/">Setting up a WordPress Animated Slider for Your Blog</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=cUzzXI7oMj8:SvzusJbSIMM:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=cUzzXI