Press Slider</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Nishtha Dosaj";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8722:"<p>A full width WordPress slider will let you show off your content in style on your website. SlideDeck3 is an excellent WordPress plugin that allows you to add a full-width slider to your website. All you need to do is enable the toolkit lens from the backend and make few easy settings in the configuration panel of the plugin.</p>\n<p>In this article, we will guide you on how to create full-width sliders in WordPress using SlideDeck3 in just a few seconds.</p>\n<h2>STEP One: Installation</h2>\n<p>First, you need to install and activate the <a title="Description of the Pinterest Addon" href="http://slidedeck.com/pricing/">SlideDeck3 Plugin</a> and the <strong>ToolKit Lens</strong>. Here is a quick tutorial on <a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/installing-lenses/ ‎">how to install lenses in WordPress using SlideDeck3</a></p>\n<h2>STEP Two: Create a full width WordPress Slider</h2>\n<p>Now it’s time to create your first full-width WordPress slider on your website using <strong>ToolKit Lens</strong>.</p>\n<p>Upon activation, you need to Visit <strong>SlideDeck3 » Manage</strong> and click <strong>Create SlideDeck </strong>under any Source either <strong>Dynamic Source or Custom Content</strong>.<strong><br />\n</strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19171 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Source-580x194.png?x36543" alt="SlideDeck3 - full width WordPress slider" width="580" height="194" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Source-580x194.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Source-768x257.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Source.png 875w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>Give a name to your slider and create a slider.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19172 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/name-1.png?x36543" alt="SlideDeck3 - full width WordPress slider" width="560" height="307" /></a></p>\n<h2>STEP Three: Integrating ToolKit Lens with Slider</h2>\n<p>Now you need to integrate your ToolKit lens with your Slider.</p>\n<p>Click <strong>Lenses</strong> under <strong>OPTIONS</strong> and Select <strong>ToolKit</strong> Lens to make a full-width slider on your site.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19176 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Lens-1-580x311.png?x36543" alt="Toolkit lens - full width WordPress slider" width="580" height="311" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Lens-1-580x311.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Lens-1-768x411.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Lens-1.png 825w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>Go to<strong> Setup Tab,</strong> Select the<strong> Full-Width </strong>option. Before you are done, we recommend you configure the dimensions of your slider.</p>\n<p>Also, configure the <strong>Height</strong> of your slider to make sure it displays in the correct symmetry. <strong><br />\n</strong></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19173 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/fullwidth-option-580x316.png?x36543" alt="SlideDeck3 - full width WordPress slider" width="580" height="316" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/fullwidth-option-580x316.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/fullwidth-option-768x418.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/fullwidth-option.png 928w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<h2>STEP Four: Configure Appearance and Navigation Settings</h2>\n<p>Go to <strong>Appearance</strong> Tab to Set <strong>Image Scaling</strong> option</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19178 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/appearence-580x572.png?x36543" alt="SlideDeck3 - full width WordPress slider" width="580" height="572" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/appearence-580x572.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/appearence.png 611w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>To make the look of your slider even better, go to <strong>Navigation</strong> Tab and select Navigation Type, Position, Style etc.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19180 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Navigation-option-580x546.png?x36543" alt="SlideDeck3 - WordPress full width slider" width="580" height="546" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Navigation-option-580x546.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Navigation-option.png 654w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<h2>STEP Five : Save Slider</h2>\n<p>Click Save <strong>SlideDeck Button</strong> to save all the settings .</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-18878 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Save_Slidedeck.png?x36543" alt="SlideDeck3 - WordPress slider" width="124" height="33" /></a></p>\n<h2>STEP Six : Add the slider to your website</h2>\n<p>Finally, it is time to add your slider to a post or page. Select any of three available ways to publish the slider on your site.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-18928 size-full" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/publish-methods.png?x36543" alt="SlideDeck3 - WordPress full width slider" width="466" height="486" /></a></p>\n<h2></h2>\n<h2>STEP Seven: View Your Full Width WordPress Slider in Action</h2>\n<p>By the end of this tutorial, you will have a full width WordPress slider that looks like <a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/demo/home/">this</a>.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19181 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/fullwidth-580x269.png?x36543" alt="SlideDeck3 - WordPress full width slider" width="580" height="269" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/fullwidth-580x269.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/fullwidth-768x356.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/fullwidth.png 1287w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>You’re all set. We hope this tutorial helped you create a full-width slider in WordPress. You might also want to check out our article on <a href="https://www.slidedeck.com/create-wordpress-rss-slider/">how to create a WordPress RSS slider</a></p>\n<p>Please let me know your feedback in the comments below.</p>\n<br/><br/><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog"><img src="//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg?x36543" alt="Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck" style="display:block;border:none;"/></a><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/creating-full-widt