l="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"madhulika";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6631:"<p>Do you want to restrict certain part of your content to registered users only?</p>\n<p><a href="https://codecanyon.net/item/userpro-user-profiles-with-social-login/5958681">UserPro Plugin</a> allows you to restrict content in WordPress with its handy feature. You can restrict users to a view a particular page content into your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>In this article, we will guide you on how to restrict content in WordPress to registered users only.</p>\n<h2>Restrict content in WordPress</h2>\n<p>First, you need to install and activate the <a href="https://codecanyon.net/item/userpro-user-profiles-with-social-login/5958681">UserPro Plugin</a>. For more details, see this step by step guide on <a title="Step by step guide on How to Install a WordPress Plugin" href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/">how to install a plugin in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>After activation, you need to visit <strong>UserPro » Restrict Content</strong> <strong>» </strong></p>\n<h2>Setting up Lock entire site feature for All Users in WordPress</h2>\n<p><strong>Go to Restrict Content</strong> <strong>» Global Restrict/Lock Settings</strong></p>\n<p>There is an option available to lock entire site for guests. Select &#8220;Yes&#8221;.</p>\n<p><a href="http://userproplugin.com/userpro/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19105 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/entire_site_lock-main-580x288.png?x36543" alt="WordPress content restriction" width="580" height="288" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/entire_site_lock-main-580x288.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/entire_site_lock-main-768x381.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/entire_site_lock-main.png 1182w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>Here you can,</p>\n<p>&#8211; Enter the Page ID that guests will be redirected to if the entire site is locked<br />\n&#8211; Enter the page ID of pages the guest users can view when all site is locked,<br />\n&#8211; Other options</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Redirect guests from homepage to custom URL</li>\n<li>Redirect members from homepage to custom URL</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href="http://userproplugin.com/userpro/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19106 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/other-setting-580x232.png?x36543" alt="WordPress content restriction" width="580" height="232" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/other-setting-580x232.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/other-setting-768x308.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/other-setting.png 1171w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<h2>Setting up Restricted Content in WordPress To Specific Users Only</h2>\n<p><strong>Restrict Content » Specific Restrict/Lock Settings</strong></p>\n<p>There are two options available to make restricted content available to specific users. You can select from the drop-down menu.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Only Verified Members</li>\n<li>All Registered Members</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After that Enter redirect URL if a whole page is locked/restricted</p>\n<h4>Restrict users from viewing content using shortcode in WordPress</h4>\n<p>This shortcode will restrict users from viewing any content entered in between shortcode :</p>\n<p><code>[userpro_private]<br />\n[userpro template=postsbyuser ]<br />\n[/userpro_private] </code></p>\n<p><strong>Restrict users from viewing content based on their role for this there is a parameter for the shortcode</strong></p>\n<p>You need to use this shortcode :</p>\n<p><code>[userpro_private restrict_to_roles=administrator,subscriber,author]<br />\n[userpro template=postsbyuser postsbyuser_type=product]<br />\n[/userpro_private] </code></p>\n<h2>Setting up Restriction for particular Page or Post</h2>\n<p>There are Four options available to restrict the page or post in a particular page to particular roles, members and verified accounts.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No restriction</li>\n<li>Restricted to All Members</li>\n<li>Restricted to Verified Accounts</li>\n<li>Restricted to User Roles</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href="http://userproplugin.com/userpro/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19108 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/page-restriction-580x179.png?x36543" alt="Page or post restriction - WordPress" width="580" height="179" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/page-restriction-580x179.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/page-restriction-768x237.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/page-restriction.png 1157w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></a></p>\n<p>With this, you are all set to set up content restriction for your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>If you have any queries please let me know in the comments below.</p>\n<br/><br/><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog"><img src="//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg?x36543" alt="Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck" style="display:block;border:none;"/></a><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/restrict-content-wordpress-registered-users/">How to restrict content in WordPress to registered users?</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=6-SBsDyJ68A:JazsFoZgrQo:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=6-SBsDyJ68A:JazsFoZgrQo:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=6-SBsDyJ68A:JazsFoZgrQo:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=6-SBsDyJ68A:JazsFoZgrQo:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=6-SBsDyJ68A:JazsFoZgrQo:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=6-SBsDyJ68A:JazsFoZgrQo:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=6-SBsDyJ68A:JazsFoZgrQo:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=6-SBsDyJ68A:JazsFoZgrQo:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Slidedeck/~4/6-SBsDyJ68A" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"https://www.slidedeck.com/restrict-content-wordpress-registered-users/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://www.slidedeck.com/restrict-content-wordpress-registered-users/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:50:"Website Comments to Improve Your WordPress Traffic";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Slidedeck/~3/kPIwWt0aXOM/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://www.slidedeck.com/website-comments-wordpress-traffic/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 09 Nov 2016 06:35:18 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"General";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Tips & Tricks";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34:"https://www.slidedeck.com/?p=18987";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:589:"<p>It’s quite disappointing to write an awesome blog post only to receive complete silence. No website comments, no shares or even tweets. How sad! This could dampen your spirit and you might even stop creating more content. This then affects your online business because it largely depends on content marketing....</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/website-comments-wordpress-traffic/">Website Comments to Improve Your WordPress Traffic</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:22:"sonal.magapu@hbwsl.com";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19894:"<p><b></b>It’s quite disappointing to write an awesome blog post only to receive complete silence. No website comments, no shares or even tweets. How sad! This could dampen your spirit and you might even stop creating more content.</p>\n<p>This then affects your online business because it largely depends on content marketing. So if you’re not creating any content your business won’t last long. So what should you do to increase traffic to your web content? The answer is using a WordPress comments plugin.</p>\n<h4 class="western" lang="en-US">Why are Website Comments Important?</h4>\n<p><img class="alignnone wp-image-18989" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Customer-Comments-Rotator.jpg?x36543" alt="website-comments" width="650" height="232" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Customer-Comments-Rotator.jpg 700w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Customer-Comments-Rotator-580x207.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></p>\n<p><b>For Increased Engagement: </b>When your site visitors make comments on your posts, you increase engagement on your site. This helps in opening up conversations and will keep people interested in coming back for more.</p>\n<p>This creates an online buzz which is really good for your website as it increases organic traffic. Comments allow site visitors to share their thoughts on what you’re discussing and even give you ideas for future blog posts.</p>\n<p><b><img class="wp-image-18992 alignright" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/download.png?x36543" alt="website comments" width="261" height="187" />To Build an Online Community: </b>When you start running a blog, you definitely want to reach out to a group of like-minded people who share the interests discussed in your blog content.</p>\n<p>In short, you want to create an online community of people interested in what you have to say. <span style="line-height: 1.5;">Comments are a great way to bring like-minded people together. </span></p>\n<p><span style="line-height: 1.5;">An online community is not only beneficial to your business but also to your site visitors who get valuable information from you.</span></p>\n<p><b>More Website Clicks:</b> When people comment on your posts and have back and forth conversations they want to keep replying to every relevant comment. This means that they have to come back to your website to leave comments.</p>\n<p>This translates to more clicks which then leads to increase ad impressions and revenue. You win, your audience wins too.</p>\n<h4 class="western" lang="en-US">Why Should You Use a WordPress Comments Plugin?</h4>\n<p><img class="alignnone wp-image-18990" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/must_have_wordpress_plugins.jpg?x36543" alt="website-comments" width="650" height="315" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/must_have_wordpress_plugins.jpg 620w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/must_have_wordpress_plugins-580x281.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><b>Set Notifications: </b>Most website comments plugins allow users to choose whether they want to receive notifications or not every time there’s a new comment on a post they are participating on or when there are replies to their comments. Other plugins will also allow users to reply to comments directly from their inbox.</p>\n<p><img class=" wp-image-18994 alignleft" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/social-media-community-Secondary.jpg?x36543" alt="website comments" width="312" height="297" /></p>\n<p><b>Multiple Login Options: </b>Comments plugins such as Livefyre and Disqus give users multiple login options.</p>\n<p>Including logging into your site using social media network details such as Facebook or Google without having to sign up on your site.</p>\n<p>Site visitors can also choose to sign in as a guest and enter a name, email and/or URL.This makes it easy for visitors to leave a quick comment on your blog posts.</p>\n<p><b>Easier to Display and Manage Comments:</b> A website comments plugin gives you more options to display and manage comments to your posts. Some plugins will allow you to display links every time someone shares your post on social media.</p>\n<p>The link will be displayed in the area beneath the comments. You also get to choose how to order your comments. This could be from oldest to newest or the other way round. You could also choose to sort by most popular or top rated comments.</p>\n<p><b>Managing Spam: </b>Plugins allow you to delete or blacklist spam and unwanted commenters. With some plugins, you can also blacklist specific words that you feel are offensive.</p>\n<p>Plugins are also great because they give you the chance to take control of a conversation that might take a wrong turn by ending website comments but still have old comments displayed.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">The good thing is that there are many high-quality plugins available that you can use for your WordPress site to make it easy for your site users to comment and to manage the interaction that takes place.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">Let’s take a look at the 10 best WordPress comments plugins available.</p>\n<h4 class="western" lang="en-US">10 Best Website Comments Plugins for WordPress</h4>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><img class="alignnone wp-image-19000" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Best-Commenting-Plugins-For-WordPress-Banner-580x305.jpg?x36543" alt="best-website comments-plugins-for-wordpress" width="650" height="341" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Best-Commenting-Plugins-For-WordPress-Banner-580x305.jpg 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Best-Commenting-Plugins-For-WordPress-Banner-768x403.jpg 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Best-Commenting-Plugins-For-WordPress-Banner.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /><br />\n<strong>1 &#8211; <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/jetpack/" target="_blank">Jetpack</a></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">This plugin is by Automattic and has multi features. The plugin offers over 20 separate functionality modules. This means Jetpack is a string of powerful plugins in one remotely managed plugin.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">The plugin has a Jetpack Comments module that turns the WordPress standard comment functionality into an expanded comments section.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">The Jetpack comments module gives your site visitors more options of signing up on your site including verification through Google+, Facebook, and Twitter. This makes it pretty easy and fast for your fans to add their thoughts to your content.<br />\n<img class=" wp-image-18996 alignright" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/disqus.png?x36543" alt="disqus comments" width="262" height="262" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/disqus.png 300w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/disqus-150x150.png 150w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/disqus-180x180.png 180w" sizes="(max-width: 262px) 100vw, 262px" /></p>\n<p><strong>2 &#8211; <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/disqus-comment-system/" target="_blank">Disqus Comment System</a></strong><br />\nDisqus is one of the most popular comments plugins. The main goal for Disqus is to make commenting on a WordPress site simple.</p>\n<p>The plugin is especially great for eliminating spam from your website comments.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">The plugin displays your comments in an elegant and well-organized way. This helps your site visitors to upvote or downvote threaded comments with much ease.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">Disqus is also a very intuitive plugin that is easy to install and will work seamlessly with your WordPress site.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><strong>3 &#8211; <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/yoast-comment-hacks/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #1155cc;"><u>Yoast Comment Hacks</u></span></a></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">Yoast comment hacks is also a very popular plugin that makes it very easy to manage website comments. The plugin makes it possible to email everyone who leaves a comment on your posts or users who have commented on a specific post.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">You can also use the plugin to send people who add a comment on a post to a thank you page or any appropriate and useful page that you want them to land on after they leave a comment.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">This helps you to send them for content that can help you convert them into business leads.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><strong><img class=" wp-image-18997 alignleft" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/com_grinapps_GetComments.png?x36543" alt="comment king plugin" width="227" height="227" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/com_grinapps_GetComments.png 300w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/com_grinapps_GetComments-150x150.png 150w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/com_grinapps_GetComments-180x180.png 180w" sizes="(max-width: 227px) 100vw, 227px" />4 &#8211; <a href="https://dealfuel.com/seller/commentking-wordpress-plugin/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #1155cc;"><u>Comment King</u></span></a></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">This is a premium plugin that works perfectly with the WordPress commenting system. It allows you to add opt-in comment forms, custom comment forms, rating forms and sales forms to build your email list.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">You can edit all the forms to make them more suitable and captivating to your audience.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">Even if you don’t have a blog, you can still use Comment King to add a comment box on your website. Your customers can use this comment box to leave a review about your product/service.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><strong>5 &#8211; <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/livefyre-comments/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #1155cc;"><u>Livefyre Comments</u></span></a></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">This a good choice if you expect or are already receiving loads of comments. Livefyre is a real-time plugin that gives you an efficient system enabling multiple users to comment at the same time.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">This WordPress comments plugin is really good for online businesses or websites that are very popular among web users such as fitness, DIY, recipe etc. You also get a pretty awesome comment moderation facility.<strong><br />\n<a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/facebook-comment-by-vivacity/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #1155cc;"><u><img class="wp-image-18998 alignright" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/commentaire-facebook-wp-580x580.jpg?x36543" alt="commentaire-facebook-wp" width="235" height="235" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/commentaire-facebook-wp-580x580.jpg 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/commentaire-facebook-wp-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/commentaire-facebook-wp-180x180.jpg 180w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/commentaire-facebook-wp-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/commentaire-facebook-wp-600x600.jpg 600w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/commentaire-facebook-wp.jpg 700w" sizes="(max-width: 235px) 100vw, 235px" /></u></span></a></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><strong>6 &#8211; <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/facebook-comment-by-vivacity/" target="_blank"><u>The Facebook Comments</u></a></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">This plugin is great if you want to keep things simple. The plugin focuses on one social channel, Facebook. Facebook also has the best user verification system making the plugin efficient.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">When you enable your Facebook fans to comment directly on your blog, you will encourage and interaction and minimize spam at the same time. This plugin also has built-in moderation options and multi-language support making it easy for you to moderate website comments.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><strong>7 &#8211; <a href="https://codecanyon.net/item/comments-lightbox-for-wordpress/13513106" target="_blank"><span style="color: #1155cc;"><u>Comments Lightbox</u></span></a></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">This premium plugin enhances your website comment process. It gives you a chance to significantly influence reach and readability of your website through increase comments.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">The plugin also avoids slow site speeds due to a lot of comments on a single page by enabling easy loading of threaded comments. The plugin displays active comments read by the user first thus generating more user engagement on your site.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><strong><img class="wp-image-18999 alignleft" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Comments-580x580.jpg?x36543" alt="website comments" width="240" height="240" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Comments-580x580.jpg 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Comments-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Comments-768x768.jpg 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Comments-180x180.jpg 180w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Comments-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Comments-600x600.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 240px) 100vw, 240px" /></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><strong>8 &#8211; <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/commentluv/" target="_blank"><u>CommentLuv</u></a></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">This plugin encourages participation by displaying a recent and relevant backlink to your audience. When a reader comments on your post, the link to their most recent blog post will be included at the end of the comment.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">This makes people more interested in posting comments on other people&#8217;s sites.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">The plugin boosts engagement and virality but tread but you have to be careful when handing out free backlinks to avoid attracting spammers. So make good use of the moderation function.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><strong>9 &#8211; <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/comment-approved/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #1155cc;"><u>Comment Approved</u></span></a></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">Comment Approved is a very reliable plugin that you can use to improve user engagement on your site. The plugin sends a notification email to people who comment on your posts letting them know that their comments have been approved for publishing.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">You can customize all notifications by making them easy to send to a user after their comment is approved.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><strong>10 &#8211; <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/akismet/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #1155cc;"><u>Akismet</u></span></a></strong></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">Our list cannot be complete if we don’t mention Akismet. This is a leading website comments plugin for WordPress. The plugin analyzes data from millions of sites making it easy to block spam on your site automatically.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">You can have a great experience even with the free version especially if you have a small site or get the pro version with more options.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><b>Conclusion</b></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US"><img class="alignnone wp-image-19001" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/customerstalking-580x319.png?x36543" alt="customers talking on website comments " width="650" height="358" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/customerstalking-580x319.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/customerstalking-768x423.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/customerstalking.png 1351w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">Allowing people to comment on websites through a website comments plugin may not be ideal for everyone but it’s a great opportunity to boost engagement and interaction with your audience.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">With a lot of options available, you will not have problems finding a good plugin that will leverage the functionality of your comment system allowing you to run your commenting process smoothly.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">The right website comments plugin for WordPress will depend on your business needs. As you choose a comment plugin, keep in mind the benefits and functionality of various plugins before settling on one.</p>\n<p class="western" lang="en-US">Take time to compare the total cost of the plugins and ease of use. Each site has its unique needs. We hope that our list above offers something for everyone!</p>\n<p><span style="border-radius: 2px; text-indent: 20px; width: auto; padding: 0px 4px 0px 0px; text-align: center; font: bold 11px/20px ''Helvetica Neue'',Helvetica,sans-serif; color: #ffffff; background: #bd081c no-repeat scroll 3px 50% / 14px 14px; position: absolute; opacity: 1; z-index: 8675309; display: none; cursor: pointer; top: 629px; left: 582px;">Save</span></p>\n<p><span style="border-radius: 2px; text-indent: 20px; width: auto; padding: 0px 4px 0px 0px; text-align: center; font: bold 11px/20px ''Helvetica Neue'',Helvetica,sans-serif; color: #ffffff; background: #bd081c  no-repeat scroll 3px 50% / 14px 14px; position: absolute; opacity: 1; z-index: 8675309; display: none; cursor: pointer; top: 2091px; left: 20px;">Save</span></p>\n<br/><br/><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog"><img src="//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg?x36543" alt="Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck" style="display:block;border:none;"/></a><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/website-comments-wordpress-traffic/">Website Comments to Improve Your WordPress Traffic</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=kPIwWt0aXOM:t_bCQNd2hVo:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=kPIwWt0aXOM:t_bCQNd2hVo:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=kPIwWt0aXOM:t_bCQNd2hVo:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=kPIwWt0aXOM:t_bCQNd2hVo:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=kPIwWt0aXOM:t_bCQNd2hVo:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http:/