your WordPress site. While it may be a difficult task, you can get it done easily with the help of WordPress plugins. UserPro Plugin allows you to easily do the same with its handy feature....</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/wordpress-redirect-after-login-setup/">How to set up a WordPress Redirect after Login for your Users</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Nishtha Dosaj";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7344:"<p>Sometimes, you may want to redirect the users to a specific page after they login to your WordPress site. While it may be a difficult task, you can get it done easily with the help of WordPress plugins.</p>\n<p><a href="http://userproplugin.com/userpro/" target="_blank">UserPro Plugin</a> allows you to easily do the same with its handy feature.</p>\n<p>In this article, we will guide you on how to set up a WordPress redirect after login for your users.</p>\n<p>First, you need to install and activate the <a href="http://userproplugin.com/userpro/" target="_blank">UserPro Plugin</a>. For more details, see this step by step guide on <a title="Step by step guide on How to Install a WordPress Plugin" href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/" target="_blank">how to install a plugin in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>Upon activation, you need to visit <strong>UserPro » Settings</strong> <strong>» Login Settings</strong></p>\n<h2>Setting up the WordPress redirect after login for your site</h2>\n<p>There are two options available to redirect the user after a successful login which you can select from the drop-down menu.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Refresh Page Only</li>\n<li>Redirect user to frontend profile</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19090 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/redirect-1-580x156.png?x36543" alt="WordPress redirect after login" width="580" height="156" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/redirect-1-580x156.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/redirect-1-768x206.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/redirect-1.png 935w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></p>\n<p>You can also <strong>redirect users to the same page after login</strong> by using this shortcode:</p>\n<p><code> [userpro template=login force_redirect_uri=1] </code></p>\n<h2>Setting up WordPress Redirect after Login for Users To a Custom URL in WordPress</h2>\n<p>You can redirect the user to particular custom URL by entering a URL in the shortcode.</p>\n<p id="Specify custom URL for login_redirect"><strong>Specify a custom URL for redirecting the user after login using login_redirect parameter in shortcode<br />\n</strong></p>\n<p>You need to use this shortcode</p>\n<p><code>[userpro template=login login_redirect=<em>http://xyz.com</em>] </code></p>\n<h2>Setting Rules for Login Redirects Based On User Roles /Single or All Users /Custom Fields.</h2>\n<p>Go to <strong>UserPro</strong> <strong> »</strong> <strong>Custom Redirects </strong><strong> »</strong> <strong>Login Redirects</strong>.</p>\n<p>Here you can create rules for login redirects based on user roles / single or all users / custom fields.</p>\n<h5>Setting up WordPress Redirect after Login based on User Role</h5>\n<p>First settings allow you to redirect specific users <strong>based on their user role</strong>.</p>\n<p>You can select a<strong> User Role</strong> from the drop-down menu. After that, you can set the <strong>Redirection URL</strong> to redirect a user after login.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19087 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/role-580x269.png?x36543" alt="WordPress redirect based on user role" width="580" height="269" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/role-580x269.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/role-768x356.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/role.png 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></p>\n<h4></h4>\n<h5>Setting up WordPress Redirect after Login based on Username</h5>\n<p>You can also set up a login redirect based on the <strong>username</strong> in WordPress. Simply select a username from the drop-down list and then enter the redirection URL.</p>\n<p>You can also select <strong>Map All Users</strong> option to simply redirect all the users to specified URL .</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19088 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/usernam-userpro-580x174.png?x36543" alt="WordPress redirect based on username" width="580" height="174" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/usernam-userpro-580x174.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/usernam-userpro-768x231.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/usernam-userpro.png 1125w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h5>Setting up WordPress Redirect after Login based on Custom Field Value</h5>\n<p>You can also set up a login redirect based on <strong>Custom field value</strong> in WordPress. Just select a custom field from the drop down list say &#8211; Firstname, put the custom field value say &#8211; John and then enter the redirect URL.</p>\n<p>So, the user with firstname John will be redirected to the specified custom URL .</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-19089 size-large" src="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/custom-field-580x296.png?x36543" alt="WordPress redirect based on custom field values" width="580" height="296" srcset="https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/custom-field-580x296.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/custom-field-768x392.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/custom-field.png 1133w" sizes="(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px" /></p>\n<p>You’re all set. We hope this tutorial helped you to learn how to redirect the user after a successful login in WordPress. Any Queries ? Please let me know in comments.</p>\n<br/><br/><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog"><img src="//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg?x36543" alt="Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck" style="display:block;border:none;"/></a><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com/wordpress-redirect-after-login-setup/">How to set up a WordPress Redirect after Login for your Users</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.slidedeck.com">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=87TQAvlDLdM:mIfN1SWH_3I:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=87TQAvlDLdM:mIfN1SWH_3I:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=87TQAvlDLdM:mIfN1SWH_3I:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=87TQAvlDLdM:mIfN1SWH_3I:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=87TQAvlDLdM:mIfN1SWH_3I:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=87TQAvlDLdM:mIfN1SWH_3I:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a